<TITLE> Mohammedan, Sonali record third successive win </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 7 (bdnews24.com)  Mohammedan Sporting Club and Sonali Bank SRC Wednesday recorded their third victory in the Premier Division Hockey League at Moulana Bhasani National Hockey Stadium. Title contenders Mohammedan beat winless Wari Club 2-0 while this season's surprising package Sonali Bank also defeated Bangladesh SC identical 2-0 at the same venue. The Motijheel-based outfit, Mohammedan, had to wait for 44 minutes to open their account with Jahid Bin Talib putting the black and white outfit ahead through a field goal. Mohammedan pressed hard on the opponent from the beginning and secured 17 penalty corners, but they converted only one in the 63rd minute with Kamruzzaman Rana scoring the team's second goal for Mohammedan. In the second match, Sonali Bank took a 1-0 lead in the first half with Alamgir Hossain giving the bankers a 33-minute lead. Krishna Kumar sealed the match for Sonali Bank in the 52nd minute through a penalty corner. 
